        "e3cdf781-1586-4bad-94d6-ba09691910ac": {
          "type": "text_block",
          "settings": {
            "width": "100%",
            "bgtext": "rgba(0,0,0,0)",
            "title_color": "#ffffff",
            "subtitle": "Process of",
            "title": "Diamond Creation",
            "size_text": "h2",
            "text": "",
            "answer_content": "<p>Every diamond begins with a carefully selected seed, chosen for its purity and potential. The seed is placed on a specialized surface and transferred into a controlled growth chamber, where carbon-rich gases are introduced. Under extreme heat and pressure—replicating natural conditions—carbon atoms gradually bond to the seed, forming a diamond crystal. Layer by layer, the diamond grows over time while experts closely monitor the entire process to ensure precision and quality. Once fully formed, the diamond is carefully extracted and then expertly cut and polished to achieve maximum brilliance, clarity, and perfection.</p>",
            "style_btn": "btn-underline btn-underline-white",
            "button": "",
            "link": "",
            "enable_padding": true,
            "block_align": "center",
            "align": "left"
          }
        }
      },
